<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[192,1440,771,987]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,348,771,795]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Comments.</emphasis>
The puparium of all known species of this genus are very dark and need to be bleached before slide mounting. The waxy secretions present on the dorsum are often difficult to remove. Description of this genus can be found in 
<bibRefCitation author="Drews, E. A. &amp; W. W. Sampson" box="[583,908,835,859]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="120 - 125" refId="ref14677" refString="Drews, E. A., and W. W. Sampson 1956. California aleyrodids of the genus Aleuropleurocelus. Annals of the Entomological Society of America 51: 120 - 125." type="journal article" year="1956">Drews and Sampson (1956)</bibRefCitation>
with discussion by 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin, J. H." box="[1137,1306,835,859]" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref15057" refString="Martin, J. H. 2005. Whiteflies of Belize (Hemiptera, Aleyrodidae) Part 2 - Introduction and account of the subfamily Aleyrodinae Westwood. Zootaxa 1098: 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="2005">Martin (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. In 
<collectingRegion box="[1347,1440,835,859]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Nevada</collectingRegion>
this genus appears to be limited to plants of the arid or semi-arid areas of the chaparral community, such as 
<taxonomicName box="[232,430,899,923]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Namaceae" genus="Eriodictyon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[232,381,899,923]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Eriodictyon</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(Yerba Santa) and desert oaks in 
<collectingRegion box="[902,1004,899,923]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Nevada</collectingRegion>
. Of the twelve known species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drews and Sampson" authorityYear="1956" box="[192,413,931,955]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Aleuropleurocelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,413,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Aleuropleurocelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, two described species occur in 
<collectingRegion box="[813,912,931,955]" country="United States of America" name="Nevada" pageId="11" pageNumber="10">Nevada</collectingRegion>
. To these are added a new species and we document one unidentified species.
</paragraph>
